## Project knowledge base

Authoritative project info lives under `.claude/knowledge/`. The agent army plugin reads these files automatically:

- [@.claude/knowledge/scope.md](.claude/knowledge/scope.md) — what this project is / isn't
- [@.claude/knowledge/context.md](.claude/knowledge/context.md) — business context, users, constraints
- [@.claude/knowledge/architecture.md](.claude/knowledge/architecture.md) — system map, data flow
- [@.claude/knowledge/data-model.md](.claude/knowledge/data-model.md) — entities + PII classification (drives security-reviewer / data-compliance)
- [@.claude/knowledge/glossary.md](.claude/knowledge/glossary.md) — domain terms
- [@.claude/knowledge/decisions/](.claude/knowledge/decisions/) — ADRs

If any of these is missing or still has its `[TODO: replace this banner ...]` marker, the agent will stop and ask you to run `/init-knowledge` and `/onboard-agent` first.

## Default routing (autonomous mode)

For any user request that **modifies code, config, schema, infrastructure, or docs**, immediately delegate to the `orchestrator` subagent via the `Agent` tool with `subagent_type: "orchestrator"`. Do NOT implement directly in the main session. The orchestrator runs the full plan → security → review → evidence chain autonomously.

**Always delegate** when the user asks to:
- Add / modify / fix / refactor / remove code
- Change config, env vars, infrastructure, CI
- Write or update tests, migrations, schemas
- "Ship", "implement", "build", "wire up", "hook up"

**Don't delegate** (answer directly in the main session) when the user asks to:
- Explain / describe / summarize code or architecture
- Show a file, search for something, read logs
- Discuss tradeoffs, brainstorm, debate approaches
- Single-line questions about how something works

If unsure, ask: "delegate to orchestrator or answer directly?" — but prefer delegation for anything that touches files.

